LLM Output Evaluator

A professional evaluation framework designed to analyze and score Large Language Model (LLM) outputs using structured rubrics and quality assessment metrics.



Overview

This repository simulates real-world AI evaluation workflows used in LLM training pipelines and AI quality assurance systems.

The project focuses on:

- Output evaluation
- Instruction-following analysis
- Hallucination detection
- Reasoning quality assessment
- Structured scoring systems
- Human feedback simulation


Objectives

The primary goal of this repository is to create a repeatable and explainable framework for evaluating AI-generated responses.

This includes:

- Identifying subtle reasoning failures
- Detecting factual inconsistencies
- Measuring response quality
- Scoring instruction adherence
- Flagging hallucination risks


